        <h2 class="fw-bold">Validator</h2>
        <p>
            <b>The Validator class provides methods for validating input data against specified rules, ensuring data integrity and correctness.</b>
            It supports various validation rules such as required fields, string validation, numeric validation, email validation, and more.
        </p>

        <h4 id="UsageExample">Usage Example</h4>
        <p>
        <pre>
if (!Validator::username($username)) throw new \Exception("Invalid username format");
